<HEADLINE> Two World Shooting Records Surpassed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Two world records were surpassed in
the Chinese National Shooting Championships which ended in Nanning
of Guangxi on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Army team totalled 1,740 points in the women's
standard rifle three by 20 event, surpassing the listed world
record of 1,738 points.
</P>
<P>
In the women's standard rifle 60 shots prone, Wang Xian
collected 597 points, surpassing the world record of 596 points.
</P>
</TEXT>
