<HEADLINE> Kinkel: Bonn Prepared to Cooperate with Kabila </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, May 21 (Xinhua) -- German Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel
said today that Germany is prepared to cooperate with the leader
of the Democratic Republic of Congo, Laurent Kabila.
</P>
<P>
But he cautioned that the country's future ties with Bonn would
depend on its democratization and free elections.
</P>
<P>
"Germany is, in principle, prepared to cooperate with the new
government in Kinshasa. Our European partners have the same
policy," said Kinkel in a statement issued in Bonn.
</P>
<P>
He said Germany accepted Kabila's pledges to hold free
elections within the next 12 months, and stressed that the pledges
must be followed by action.
</P>
<P>
"We will make our further cooperation with Kabila's government
dependent on implementation of the announced democratization steps
which must end up with a free, general elections," he said.
</P>
<P>
If the country was to succeed in its new start, there should be
no further acts of revenge as had taken place in recent days.
</P>
<P>
Kabila announced on May 17 that he would be president of Zaire after
toppling former president, Mobuto Sese Seko. 
</P>
</TEXT>
