<HEADLINE> World Bank Approves Huge Financing for India's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, May 21 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank today announced
the approval of a 325 million U.S. dollar assistance package to
India for an irrigation project to boost Andhra Pradesh's
agricultural production.
</P>
<P>
The package includes a 175 million loan which will be provided
by the International Bank For Reconstruction and Development and a
150 million dollar credit which will be channeled through the
International Development Association, the World Bank's
concessionary lending arm.
</P>
<P>
The project will increase the agricultural productivity of more
than 310,000 hectares and therefore raise the income of mostly
marginal and small farmers.
</P>
<P>
The total cost of the project is estimated at some 477.43
million dollars. In addition to the World Bank's financing, the
government of Andhra Pradesh will contribute the remaining 152.43
million dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
