<DOCNO> XIE19970522.0018 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Britain to Ban Landmine Manufacture, Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, May 21 (Xinhua) -- British Prime Minister Tony Blair
said today his government will ban the import, export and
manufacture of landmines.
</P>
<P>
An official statement on the ban of anti-personal mines will be
announced later, Blair told a parliament meeting.
</P>
<P>
This marks a significant change from the policy of the previous
Conservative government. The former administration, although
dedicated to destroying existing stocks of landmines, insisted on
retaining options to buy the so-called "smart mines" which destroy
themselves after a set period.
</P>
<P>
Officials said Britain intended to sign up to the so-called
Ottawa Process, a Canadian initiative which groups 50 nations who
want to sign a treaty by the end of this year to ban the
production, stockpiling, export and use of mines.
</P>
<P>
Britain would destroy all its stocks of anti-personnel
landmines by 2005 and would scrap the idea of replacing them with
smart mines, the officials said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
