<HEADLINE> Greece Condemns Turkish "Invasion" in Northern Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Greece today expressed its "strong
opposition" to the "invasion" of Turkish troops in northern Iraq,
and called for an immediate withdrawal of the troops from the
region.
</P>
<P>
The Greek Foreign Ministry said that Turkey should stop
creating situations reminiscent of other times "at the expense of
its neighbors."
</P>
<P>
"It is with concern that the Greek government ascertains that
Turkey, while continuing to occupy part of the Cyprus Republic,
has formulated a repetitive practice which deals a blow to
international legality and threatens the stability of the border
region," the ministry said.
</P>
<P>
The ministry also called on Turkey to respect the territorial
integrity, sovereignty and security of Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Iraq's envoy to Greece, Issam Khalil, today appealed to the
international community and the Greek government to condemn the
Turkish thrust into northern Iraq and the policy of "double
Standards" in international relations. 
</P>
