<HEADLINE> US Long-Distance Phone Giant to Enter Local Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, May 21 (Xinhua) -- The AT&AMP;T Corporation, the largest
long-distance telephone company in the United States, reached
Tuesday an agreement with Nynex Corporation, a big local phone
company in New York state, to connect the two companies' networks
in New York state.
</P>
<P>
By securing Nynex's cooperation, AT&AMP;T would be able to enter
the country's most lucrative local telephone market, the New York
Times commented in a report referring to the forging of
partnership between the long-distance giant and the local phone
company.
</P>
<P>
AT&AMP;T is expected to focus on providing service to businesses in
New York City, turning Nynex to residential customers.
</P>
<P>
On the same day, Nynex reached a tentative agreement with MCI
Communications Corporation, another long-distance phone giant, on
opening its network to that company.
</P>
<P>
For Nynex, reaching interconnection deals with long-distance
companies is an essential part of its strategy to enter the
long-distance businesses itself, the report observed.
</P>
<P>
AT&AMP;T had already reached such agreements in 12 other states.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
