<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Stresses Principles for Humanitarian Aid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, May 21 (xinhua) -- Compliance with the purposes
and principles of the UN Charter, particularly respect for state
sovereignty and for the views of the states and parties concerned,
and strict neutrality remain important principles for
international aid to refugees and displaced persons, Chinese
Ambassador Wang Xuexian said here today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the UN Security Council on the protection of
humanitarian assistance to refugees and others in conflict
situations, he said that the solution and the provision of
humanitarian assistance to refugees are the common responsibility
of the international community as a whole.
</P>
<P>
"As far as the United Nations is concerned, humanitarian
activities should mainly be taken by the relevant departments and
agencies, while the Security Council should mainly involve itself
with the settlement of political and security-related issues," he
said.
</P>
<P>
The political will and willingness to cooperate on the part of
the states and parties concerned are the key to the success of
conflict resolution and humanitarian assistance, he said.
</P>
<P>
The international community should make greater efforts to
promote peace, he said, adding that resolution of conflicts by
such peaceful means as good offices, mediation and negotiations is
in itself an effective way to protect refugees.
</P>
<P>
On the tendency toward frequently invoking Chapter 7 of the UN
Charter or even authorizing the use of force in peace-keeping and
humanitarian relief, he said, the approach will more often than
not further complicate problems.
</P>
<P>
"When the use of force is indeed necessary for the protection
of the delivery of humanitarian relief and the safety and freedom
of movement of UN peace-keepers, the authorization to use force
must be strictly confined to self-defense," he said.
</P>
<P>
He also stressed "preventive development" but said "preventive
deployment" is being much talked about. The international
community should make great efforts to eradicate the root causes
of refugees by encouraging national unity, promoting economic
development and maintaining national stability, Wang said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
