<HEADLINE> CDB's 27th Annual Meeting Opens in Toronto </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TORONTO, May 21 (Xinhua) -- The 27th annual Board of Governors
meeting of the Caribbean Development Bank (CDB) opened today in
Canada's largest city of Toronto.
</P>
<P>
China's application for admission into the CDB as a
non-regional, non-borrowing member is among the items to be
addressed at the two-day meeting.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is also expected to discuss its strong financial
performance and examine issues related to the use of its net
profit.
</P>
<P>
Founded in 1969, the CDB is a major financer of infrastructure
and social sector development projects and promotes regional
integration in the Caribbean community.
</P>
<P>
Currently it is composed of 17 regional borrowing members,
three regional non-borrowing members and five non-regional
members.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time that the CDB has held its annual
meetings outside of the Caribbean region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
