<HEADLINE> Land Mine Blast Kills 2 Children in Egypt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Two children were killed and three
others along with a woman injured as a land mine left over from
past wars in the mountainous area west of Suez Canal went off,
the Egyptian Interior Ministry said today.
</P>
<P>
According to the surviving children, a "queer object" they had
found went off while they were tampering with it, the ministry
said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
The injured were admitted into a nearby hospital for treatment
in Ismalia, about 120 kilometers east of Cairo. The prosecution
have been notified for investigations.
</P>
<P>
Many land mines were left unexploded in the desert of the Sinai
peninsula and nearby areas when Arab countries fought against
Israel during the Middle East wars in 1956, 1967 and 1973. 
</P>
</TEXT>
