<HEADLINE> CCP Congratulates Mozambique's Party Congress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, May 21 (Xinhua) -- The Communist Party of China has
sent a delegation to attend the seventh national congress of the
ruling Mozambican Liberation Front party.
</P>
<P>
A Chinese communist party delegation headed by Liu Jingqin
today heaped its warm congratulations on the Mozambican party's
ongoing national congress which started on Monday.
</P>
<P>
A message of congratulations from the Central Committee of the
Chinese Communist Party, which was read by Liu Jingqin at the
meeting, hailed the achievements made by the Mozambique's ruling
party and the Mozambican people in realizing national
reconciliation and domestic peace, recovering its economy and
reconstructing the war-torn country.
</P>
<P>
It believed that the Mozambican Liberation Front Party will
lead its people to make greater achievements in building their
country by seeking a path of development in line with their
specific national conditions.
</P>
<P>
The message also hoped that the traditional friendship and
goodwill cooperation between the two parties will be further
enhanced and consolidated.
</P>
<P>
This national congress will formulate the ruling Mozambican
party's plan of action and policy for next five years, revise the
party program and constitution and elect new leadership of the
party.
</P>
<P>
A total of 1,000 deputies are participating in the congress
which is due to end on Saturday. At the congress, 15 delegations
sent by parties of foreign countries, including the Chinese
delegation which arrived here last Sunday, are also present as
observers.
</P>
<P>
The Liberation Front Party of mozambique, founded in 1962, has
more than one million members at present. Its last national
congress was held in August 1991. 
</P>
</TEXT>
