<HEADLINE> Bonn to Continue Subsidizing Economy in E.Germany </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Chancellor Helmut Kohl's government
today declared continuation of subsidizing the housing
construction and machinery sectors in eastern Germany beyond the
year 2002 as part of efforts to ease high unemployment in the
area.
</P>
<P>
Economics Minister Guenter Rexrodt told reporters in Bonn,
"This is a signal for (investors) in all of Germany that we are
taking on the problem."
</P>
<P>
He said the annual subsidies for building inner-city
apartments, industrial buildings and for buying factory machinery
in eastern Germany would be reduced to 4.4 billion marks (2.6
billion U.S. dollars) from 2002 from the current 5.7 billion marks
(3.4 billion dollars).
</P>
<P>
This plan serves as part of a broader program that Kohl is due
to unveil in Berlin Thursday which is aimed at creating 100,000
additional jobs per year in eastern Germany.
</P>
<P>
Official data showed joblessness in eastern Germany was 17.5
percent in April, compared with 9.8 percent in western Germany and
a national average of 11.3 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
