<HEADLINE> Cyprus International State Fair Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, May 21 (Xinhua) -- The 22nd Cyprus International
State Fair opened here this evening with emphasis on promoting the
island further as a transit center for economic activities.
</P>
<P>
Addressing at the opening of the fair, Cyprus President
Glafcos Clerides said, "the government's ambition is to promote
Cyprus even further as a transit center and base for carrying out
other economic activities," as the island is located at the
crossroads of three continents.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that Cyprus' excellent relations with the
Middle East, the Balkans and Eastern Europe, its European course
and its excellent infrastructure in human and material resources
are assets that make it a singular base for economic and
business activities.
</P>
<P>
The President also noted that Cyprus' accession to the
European Union will create significant advantages for the
economies of its friendly neighboring countries.
</P>
<P>
Also speaking at the opening ceremony, Minister of Commerce,
Industry and Tourism, Kyriakos Christofi said the fair "reflects
and projects not only the achievements of manufacture and the
economic activity and development of the island in general, but
in particular the Cypriot businessman's industrial and commercial
dynamism".
</P>
<P>
He noted that in 1996 total imports reached 1.86 billion Cyprus
pounds (3.92 billion dollars), showing an 11.2 percent increase
compared with 1995, whereas total exports were about 650 million
Cyprus pounds (1300 million dollars), an increase of 16.8
percent, Christofi explained.
</P>
<P>
The Minister also said that re-exports showed a rapid
increase, reaching 420 million Cyprus pounds (840 million
dollars), but exports of local products remained at 1996 levels.
</P>
<P>
A total of 1,600 local and 40 foreign companies from 17
countries are participating in this year's International State
Fair. 
</P>
</TEXT>
