<HEADLINE> IDB Approves 28 Mln Dlrs to Boost Education in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, May 21 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American Development
Bank (IDB) today approved a 28 million U.S. dollar loan to Costa
Rica to improve the quality, efficiency and equity of preschool
and lower secondary education.
</P>
<P>
The project has two components: expansion of preschool
education in low-income urban and rural communities and the
broadening of educational opportunities in rural areas in grades 7
through 9, Costa Rica's "third cycle."
</P>
<P>
The main goals of the project are to broaden the coverage of
preschool education by 5,880 pupils a year and provide educational
facilities to another 2,350 preschool children now in premises
that are lent. Coverage of the third cycle will be widened by
9,067 students a year and the dropout and repetition rates in the
third cycle are expected to fall drastically in rural areas.
</P>
<P>
The total cost of the project is estimated at 40 million
dollars. Apart from the IDB loan, local counterpart funds total 12
million dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
