<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China, Algeria to Cooperate in Nuclear Energy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALGIERS, May 21 (Xinhua) -- China and Algeria signed an
agreement here today to beef up their cooperation in the field of
nuclear energy.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was signed Cao Yicheng, director of Chinese
Engineering Company for Nuclear Energy, and Abu Bakr Bin Buzeid,
Algerian Minister of Higher Education and Scientific Research.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement China
will provide Algeria with the blueprints and plan of the third
stage of construction of the Algerian Center of Nuclear Energy
Research.
</P>
<P>
The third stage comprises projects for control of isotopes,
radiation and poison, in addition to the treatment of lost water
and waste.
</P>
<P>
The Algerian center of nuclear energy research which is under
construction will be subject to inspection by the International
Atomic Energy Agency. 
</P>
