<HEADLINE> US PC Computer Quarterly Profit up 141 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, May 21 (Xinhua) -- The Dell Computer Corporation, one
of the fast-growing personal computer companies in the United
States, reported Tuesday fiscal first quarter earnings that
exceeded the previous estimates, as its sales growth outpaced that
of other personal computer makers in the country.
</P>
<P>
For the quarter, which ended on May 4, Dell reported earnings
of 198 million U.S. dollars, more than twice the 82 million U.S.
dollars it reported in the comparable period a year earlier. Sales
grew 58 percent, to 2.59 billion U.S. dollars from 1.64 billion
U.S. dollars a year earlier, according to a report of the New York
Times today.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said that Dell had benefited from excellent execution
of its direct-sale strategy, which allows it to undercut some of
competitors by avoiding dealer markups.
</P>
<P>
Michael Dell, Dell's chairman and chief executive said that his
company' goal is to take the Dell direct model to the next level,
and the Internet and value-added services represent excellent
opportunities to achieve that goal.
</P>
<P>
The Compaq Computer Corporation, the largest personal computer
maker in the country, is working to understand and emulate Dell
model in an effort to enter the direct sales business, the report
revealed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
