<HEADLINE> Kabila Postpones Formation of New Cabinet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
(by Guo Ming)
</P>
<P>
KINSHASA, May 21 (Xinhua) --Laurent Kabila, Head of State of
the new-born Democratic Republic of Congo has postponed to
declare his new government of national salvation, originally
scheduled for today.
</P>
<P>
Kabila, who arrived at capital Kinshasa last night from his
military headquarters in the southern city of Lubumbasi, has not
made any public appearance today.
</P>
<P>
He has spent the whole day in the residence of former Prime
Minister General Likulia Bolongo in the suburbs of Kinshasa,
meeting with his new cabinet members, some of whom are already
known to the public, and with various political leaders.
</P>
<P>
He also presided over an urgent military meeting to discuss
the continued warfare in the western Lower Zaire Province between
Kabila's troops and soldiers loyal to exiled former president
Mobutu Sese Seko.
</P>
<P>
Foreign journalists and diplomats waited for a whole day today
for an announcement of the formation of the new cabinet.
</P>
<P>
Repeatedly asked when the new government will be formed, one
of Kabila's aides said: "Any time from now."
</P>
<P>
Kabila and his soldiers waged a seven-month war to finally
topple the Mobutu administration on May 17 when troops of his
Alliance of Democratic Forces for the Liberation of Congo-Zaire
(ADFL) "liberated" Kinshasa, thus controlling 90 percent of the
Africa's third largest country.
</P>
<P>
On the same day, he declared himself to be the head of state
and changed the country name from Zaire to the Democratic
Republic of Congo. 
</P>
</TEXT>
