<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Feature: Unbreakable Bond of Love </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 22 (Xinhua) -- For 58-year-old Awahan, a typical
day is spent in doing chores both in the field and the
house. Unlike most peasant women in her village in the northwest
region of Xinjiang, she has a special job, namely, to dress and
feed her 29-year-old daughter.
</P>
<P>
Daughter Abigul, possessing a height of only one meter and the
intelligence equal to a four year old, has been confined in a
wheelchair all her life due to a damaged spine.
</P>
<P>
"The girl has really been pampered,"Awahan complains
lovingly. "She only eats fine rice and flour, and insists on
having her clothes changed every three days."
</P>
<P>
Indeed, Abigul has been the center of Awahan's love as well as
that of her family ever since the day she adopted the abandoned
child 29 years ago.
</P>
<P>
Longing to have a child, a young Uygur couple living in the
outskirts of Fukang, about 60 kilometers east of the regional
capital of Urumqi, adopted a five-month-old Han baby girl in 1968.
</P>
<P>
"We named the baby Abigul, meaning golden flower, hoping she
will grow to be as beautiful as a golden flower," Awahan recalled.
</P>
<P>
However, the couple soon began to worry about the baby's
inability to sit up, then to stand up and talk. One doctor said
the baby had calcium deficiency, so Awahan fed her calcium tablets
and calcium-rich foods, but to no avail.
</P>
<P>
Years passed with Awahan carrying the child to every doctor she
could think of, and Abigul was finally diagnosed in a Urumqi
hospital as a victim of a spine fracture at birth. Then, Abigul
was 15 years old, and Awahan knew her only child would never stand
up.
</P>
<P>
"I was not exactly devastated by the news, as you might think,"
Awahan said. "Perhaps I was too tired to be, or perhaps I had sort
of suspected it for a long time."
</P>
<P>
She had tried her best over the years -- selling every object
of value in her house for the money to pay medical treatment for
Abigul, and borrowing money from every possible source.
</P>
<P>
"During the worst time, there was only a table left in the
house," she recounted.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970522.0078 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-22 </DATE_TIME>
