<HEADLINE> IMF Approves Extension of Stand-By Credit to Djibouti </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, May 22 (Xinhua) -- The International Monetary Fund
(IMF) today approved a request by the government of Djibouti to
extend the current stand-by credit through end-March 1998, and to
augment the credit.
</P>
<P>
The IMF Executive Board okayed a stand-by credit for an amount
equivalent to about 6.4 million U.S. dollars on April 15, 1996.
The newly augmented amount available under the stand-by credit is
by about 2.8 million dollars as an effort to support the
government's economic and financial program for 1997.
</P>
<P>
Djibouti, a tiny country in northeastern Africa, joined the IMF
in December 1978. Its quota is about 16 million dollars. 
