<HEADLINE> China Tightens Coal Production Order </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Illegal coal production must be
stopped, vice-premier Wu Bangguo said in a televised conference
today.
</P>
<P>
The coal industry is China's basic industry and both the Party
and the State Council have put great emphasis on its development,
Wu, also a member of the Political Bureau of the Communist Party
of China (CPC) Central Committee, said.
</P>
<P>
Wu noted that great concern must be given to problems existing
in coal industry, especially those in the township-run coal mines
such as illegal mining, poor production conditions, frequent
accidents, backward mining methods, and low usage rates.
</P>
<P>
A nationwide campaign will be conducted within a period of time
to rectify the coal production order, he said, saying that the
emphasis of the rectification will be put on unlicensed
township-level coal mines.
</P>
<P>
Wu Bangguo asked the governments at all levels to put the work
on their agenda and implement it earnestly.
</P>
<P>
The conference was held jointly by the Ministry of Coal
Industry, the State Economic and Trade Commission, the Ministry of
Labor, the Ministry of Geology and Mineral Resources, the Ministry
of Supervision, and the All-China Federation of Trade Unions.
</P>
</TEXT>
