<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Urges Financial Institutions to Implement Internal Control </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 22 (Xinhua) -- China's central bank has issued a
notice recently urging all commercial financial institutions to
establish an internal control system.
</P>
<P>
Internal control of financial institutions is
self-disciplinary, the People's Bank of China said in the notice.
</P>
<P>
To improve internal control among financial institutions is an
important component of financial supervision and is the keystone
to standardize the activities of financial institutions and to
reduce risks, the notice pointed out.
</P>
<P>
Internal control of financial institutions includes controling
the internal organizational structure, trading risks, trading in
financial derivatives, bank credit and insurance fund risks, the
notice said.
</P>
<P>
Internal control also covers the accounting system, power
authorization, and the computerized business system, the central
bank added.
</P>
<P>
Financial institutions should set up a progressive three-level
monitoring net and introduce a position-linked responsibility
system, the central bank noted.
</P>
<P>
It also urged the financial institutions to establish a
complete information storing system and record all business
activities in a honest, detailed, and timely manner.
</P>
<P>
An effective preventive and warning system should be put into
place to ensure that immediate, proper measures can be taken when
necessary, the notice urged, adding that the proper supervisory
means should be reinforced and improved.
</P>
<P>
The notice said that how internal control is done will be taken
into account when commercial financial institutions are examined
by the central bank.
</P>
<P>
The central bank will order those financial institutions with
problems in internal control to straighten things out and punish
those with serious problems.
</P>
<P>
When long-term poor internal control or lax implementation of
control measures result in great economic losses or financial
crimes, the central bank will disqualify the senior management
personnel believed to be responsible for the posts they hold for a
period of time or for life, the notice said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
