<HEADLINE> China Prepares for Summer Grains Purchase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 22 (Xinhua) -- The General Office of the State
Council, China's cabinet, today issued a circular, urging
governments across the country to attach importance to the summer
agricultural production and the state purchase of grains and oils.
</P>
<P>
The circular said that the planting area for summer grains has
increased this year, and a summer harvest is already in sight as
all grain and oil crops have to date been growing very well.
</P>
<P>
"Success in the promotion of the summer agricultural production
and in the purchase of grains and oils is connected with harvests
for the whole year, as well as the farmers' farming enthusiasm and
sustained and steady agricultural development," it noted.
</P>
<P>
It required that all regions and relevant departments strictly
follow the instructions of the Party Central Committee and the
State Council, and take effective steps to ensure the summer
harvest and successful purchase of grains and oils.
</P>
<P>
"Governments at all levels across the country must have a clear
understanding of the possible difficulties facing this year's
summer grains and oils purchase, and make full preparations in
various aspects, such as reaping of the crops and storage of
purchased grains," it said.
</P>
<P>
It went on to say that governments at all levels must guarantee
the special fund for the purchase of grains and oils, while all
financial departments and relevant banks should be responsible for
the timely and sufficient supply of money.
</P>
<P>
"It is absolutely forbidden to give the farmers any IOUs," the
circular stressed.
</P>
<P>
It also reminded various regions and departments of paying
equal attention to the sowing of autumn crops, so as to lay a
solid foundation for the autumn harvest. 
</P>
</TEXT>
