<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Financial Institutions Urged to Set up Internal Control System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 22 (Xinhua) -- The People's Bank of China, China's
central bank, has urged financial institutions across the country
to fully establish a system of internal control, to ensure a safe
and smooth development for the financial sector.
</P>
<P>
According to an official with the central bank, the internal
control for financial institutions mainly refers to control over
the institutions' internal organizing structure, risks in capital
trade, trading of financial derivatives, risks of loans, risks of
insurance fund, as well as control of the accounting system, of
authorization and accreditation, and of the business computer
system.
</P>
<P>
"The system of internal control is a kind of self-disciplinary
activity of the financial institutions, which can help standardize
their management and prevent risks effectively," said the official.
</P>
<P>
He said that the central bank has also issued a document,
titled "Guiding principles for the strengthening of the internal
control in the financial institutions".
</P>
<P>
The document requires, through the introduction of an internal
control system, that the financial institutions must guarantee
that national laws and regulations and supervisory rules of the
central bank be implemented in full, various risks be limited, and
the institutions' self-development strategies and management goals
be achieved.
</P>
<P>
According to this document, the central bank, besides examining
the financial institutions' business operations, should also take
the responsibility of correcting the internal control situation in
these institutions.
</P>
<P>
"The central bank can suggest a rectification to any financial
institution that has problems with the internal control, and
punish those with serious problems," the document added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
