<TEXT>
<P>
ISALAMBAD, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Fighting is continuing in Baghlan
province of northern Afghanistan between the Islamic militia
Taliban and forces loyal to Uzbek warlord Rashid Dostum, Afghan
sources said today.
</P>
<P>
The pro-Taliban forces have taken at least two northern
provincial capitals with the revolt against Dostum spreading from
Kunduz to Baghlan province, said the Afghan sources in Peshawar,
Pakistan's northwestern city.
</P>
<P>
The embattled Dostum is consolidating his positions around his
headquarters Mazar-e-Sharif in Balkh province, they said.
</P>
