Masood, former military chief of the ousted Afghan government, has
already drawn up an exit route in case Mazar-e-Sharif falls to the
Taliban.
</P>
<P>
The sources said another Dostum's major ally, Jaffar Nadari,
governor of Baghlan province, also shifted to the Taliban's ranks.
</P>
<P>
Early this week, Abdul Malik, right-hand man of Dostum,
defected to the Taliban in the northwestern province of Faryab,
which allowed the militia to have made major gains in northern
Afghanistan after almost six-month stalemate.  
