<DOCNO> XIE19970522.0111 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jordan Seeks to Postpone Repayment of Huge Debt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, May 22 (Xinhua) - Jordan is seeking to postpone the
repayment to Western creditors its huge debt, which now accounts
for 90 percent of the gross national product (GNP), to help speed
up its ongoing economic reform.
</P>
<P>
The kingdom, with its official debt reaching 6.5 billion
U.S. dollars, will try to persuade the Paris Club, an non-official
organization devoted to help the developing countries delay paying
debt to Western creditors, to help it reschedule 1.2 billion
dollars of debt that should be repaid between June 1997 and June
2000, a government minister said.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting scheduled for May 22, Jordan is optimistic
that it will convince the Paris Club to accept the kingdom's
request, said Deputy Prime Minister for Development Affairs and
Minister of State for Prime Ministry Affairs Jawad Anani, in an
interview with Jordan Times, the country's sole English daily.
</P>
<P>
"The economic steps the kingdom has undertaken recently, such
as reducing the deficit in its annual budget, increasing exports
and the privatization process, will facilitate the approval of
Jordan's request," the deputy prime minister said.
</P>
<P>
Jordan's economic performance in the past three years will also
assure its major creditors of its ability to repay the money,
Anani said.
</P>
<P>
If the rescheduling is realized, it will help Jordan reduce its
debt repayment burden and cushion the impact of the International
Monetary Fund-directed economic reforms, he added.
</P>
<P>
Jordan's first restructuring of its debt was in 1989 after an
economic crisis which forced the International Monetary Fund to
intervene as the kingdom failed to service eight billion dollars
of foreign debt.
</P>
<P>
Jordan, with scant natural resources and oil but more than 4
million people, makes limited money from tourism, phosphate
production, export of highly-educated personnel and transit
trade. But it managed to flourish among the Arab states depending
largely on foreign aid.
</P>
<P>
The United States, Japan, Germany and Italy are the most
important aid contributors to Jordan. They stopped to provide aid
after the outbreak of the Gulf crisis in 1990, when Jordan sided
with Iraq that invaded neighboring Kuwait.
</P>
<P>
After the crisis, Jordan distanced itself from Iraq and the
contributors then began to give it aid again. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970522.0112 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin Meets CPC Delegates of Beijing Military Area Command </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Jiang Zemin, general secretary of
the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee and chairman
of the Central Military Commission (CMC), said here today that the
army must adhere to Deng Xiaoping's theory of building socialism
with Chinese characteristics and his thoughts in army building
during the new era, and carefully study the new situation and
issues.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the remarks when meeting with the delegates to the
Seventh CPC Congress of the Beijing Military Area Command this
evening.
</P>
<P>
Jiang praised the CPC Committee of Beijing Military Area
Command for earnestly carrying out the guidelines and decisions of
the CPC Central Committee and CMC in recent years, leading the
command to work actively, and accomplishing new tasks.
</P>
<P>
Jiang noted that the Beijing Military Area Command is of
strategic importance and shoulders an immense responsibility.
</P>
<P>
He asked the military area command to continue to give top
priority to the ideological and political building, strengthen the
building of Party organizations at all levels as well as education
and administration of high- and medium-level cadres, ensure the
Party's absolute leadership over the army, ensure the army's
high-level stability and unity, and work hard to master the modern
technology required to win high-tech battles, and complete every
task of the CPC Central Committee and the CMC.
</P>
<P>
The Seventh Party Congress of the Beijing Military Area Command
opened in Beijing on May 21, participated by 700 delegates.
</P>
<P>
Liu Huaqing, member of the Standing Committee of the CPC
Central Committee and vice CMC chairman, Zhang Wannian and Chi
Haotian, both vice CMC chairmen, attended the meeting today.
</P>
