<HEADLINE> Preparatory Committee Holds Ninth Plenum in Beijing (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 22 (Xinhua) -- The ninth plenary session of the
Preparatory Committee for the Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region (SAR) began today in the Great Hall of the People in
Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The two-day session will discuss specific methods for forming
the first Legislative Council of the Hong Kong SAR, suggestions on
what national laws shall be added to or deleted from Annex 3 of
the Basic Law, and decisions on the swearing-in ceremony of
relevant Hong Kong SAR personnel when taking office.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-Premier Qian Qichen delivered a speech at the
meeting, saying the Preparatory Committee has accomplished most of
its tasks.
</P>
<P>
These tasks include forming the Selection Committee for the
First Government of the Hong Kong SAR, electing the candidate of
the first Chief Executive of the Hong Kong SAR, and choosing the
Provisional Legislative Council, he said.
</P>
<P>
This fully shows the determination and sincerity of the Central
People's Government in implementing the principles of "one
country, two systems", "Hong Kong people governing Hong Kong", and
a high-degree of autonomy in Hong Kong, and has enhanced the
confidence of the Hong Kong people and the international community
about Hong Kong's future, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Qian, who is also chairman of the Preparatory Committee, said
the Provisional Legislative Council has won increasingly
extensive recognition, despite the non-cooperative attitude of the
British Hong Kong authorities.
</P>
<P>
The specific methods for forming the first Legislative Council
of the Hong Kong SAR that the Preparatory Committee has worked on
in recent months will reflect the principles of democracy,
fairness, and openness, he said.
</P>
<P>
Anyone who accords with the qualifications and requirements
prescribed in the Basic Law and the relevant decision of the
National People's Congress, is eligible to run for the election of
the Legislative Council member, he stressed.
</P>
<P>
He said how to elect the first Legislative Council should be
taken into consideration not only by the Preparatory Committee,
but also by the executive institution and legislature of the Hong
Kong SAR, adding that they should also be responsible for
organizing the election.
</P>
</TEXT>
