<DOCNO> XIE19970522.0125 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Singapore Ratifies Chemical Weapons Convention </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Singapore ratified the Convention
on the Prohibition of the Development, Production, Stockpiling and
Use of Chemical Weapons and on Their Destruction, which is also
known as "The Chemical Weapons Convention" (CWC), in New York on
May 21, the Foreign Ministry announced here today.
</P>
<P>
"Singapore's ratification of the CWC demonstrates its
commitment to the objectives of the Convention which are to
eliminate the use of chemical weapons, without hampering the
activities of civilian chemical industries and technological
development," the ministry said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
Under the CWC, Singapore will set up the necessary machinery to
control the production, consumption, import and export, as well as
verification of toxic chemicals and precursors, it said.
</P>
<P>
Singapore is also required to conduct inspection in Singapore
of facilities which are governed by the CWC and to take action
against offenders should there be any violation of the provisions
of the Convention, the ministry said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
