<HEADLINE> Bahrain Backs Syria's Position on Mideast Peace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Bahraini leaders have told the
visiting Syrian Vice President Abdul-Halim Khaddam that Bahrain
supports the Syrian position on the Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
This was announced in a press statement made by Khaddam in
Manama today after holding talks with Bahraini leaders, according
to reports monitored here.
</P>
<P>
Khaddam expressed his satisfaction with the outcome of the
talks he had with Bahraini leaders, pointing out that the
views of both sides on the issues considered by them were
concurrent.
</P>
<P>
The Syrian Vice President praised Bahrain's position on the
Middle East peace process, adding that it is in perfect agreement
with those of Syria and the other Arab states.
</P>
<P>
Khaddam made it clear that Syrian President Hafez Al-Assad's
message handed by him to Emir of Bahrain Isa Bin Suleiman al
Khalifa dealt with the Middle East peace problems and the
developments in the region.
</P>
<P>
"In the light of Israel's intransigent position on the peace
process, the Arab nation has decided to halt normalization and
all forms of cooperation with Israel," Khaddam said.
</P>
<P>
"Syria collaborates with Arab states for putting resolutions
of the recent Arab summit, as well as those of Arab foreign
ministers and the recent OIC, into practice, because there should
be a unified Arab stand against Israeli intransigence, with the
aim of protecting Arab interests and rights," he added.
</P>
<P>
Bahraini capital Manama is the last leg of his five-gulf-nation
tour which also took him to Saudi Arabia, Kuwait, the United Arab
Emirates and Oman.
</P>
<P>
During his visit to the gulf states, Khaddam urged the Gulf
leaders to support the delay of the Doha Mideast-North African
economic summit due to be held next November with the
participation of Israel.
</P>
<P>
local press said today that the Gulf Cooperation Council
(GCC) foreign ministers would consider to postpone the summit to
June next year. 
</P>
