<HEADLINE> EP's Invitation to Taiwan's "Foreign Minister" Denounced </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 22 (Xinhua) -- China firmly opposes and expresses
its strong indignation against the European Parliament Foreign
Affairs Committee's invitation to John Chang, Taiwan's so-called
"foreign minister", to conduct any activity in the European
Parliament on May 22.
</P>
<P>
In response to a reporter's question at today's routine press
conference, Foreign Ministry Spokesman Shen Guofang said the
European Parliament's action is open support for the attempt of
the Taiwan authorities to create "two Chinas" and "one China, one
Taiwan", and a serious infringement upon in China's sovereignty
and gross interference in China's internal affairs.
</P>
<P>
Shen noted that there is only one China in the world and the
government of the People's Republic of China is the sole
legitimate government representing the whole China with Taiwan as
an inalienable part of it.
</P>
<P>
Recognizing and observing the "one China" principle is the
basis for the establishment of diplomatic ties and development of
relations between China and the European Union (EU), as well as EU
member states, he said.
</P>
<P>
China admonish some people in the European Parliament to
scrupulously abide by principles set for China-EU diplomatic
relations in real earnest and to stop doing anything that will
undermine China's reunification and Sino-EU relations, Shen said.
</P>
<P>
