Kong have already reached agreement with the Chinese government to
maintain such representation in the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (HKSAR). Some of them have sent the names
and resumes of the candidates who will remain at the post of heads
of consulates in the HKSAR after July 1 to the Chinese Foreign
Ministry through diplomatic channels.
</P>
<P>
