<HEADLINE> Tung Chee Hwa Welcomes Australia's Decision on HKSAR Passports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 22 (Xinhua) -- The Chief Executive of the Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR), Tung Chee Hwa, today
welcomed the announcement by the Australian government accepting
the Hong Kong SAR passports for visa-issuing purposes from July 1.
</P>
<P>
An announcement from the Chief Executive's Office noted the
Australian government's statement that HKSAR passports would have
the same visa validity as the current BN(O) passports.
</P>
<P>
"The Australian government's decision in regard to holders of
HKSAR passports is particularly welcome in view of the strong
business and social links between us," Tung said.
</P>
<P>
"Australian citizens are invited to continue enjoying Hong
Kong's attractions as a major international business, financial
and tourism center," he said.
</P>
<P>
He added that the sound reasoning behind this decision will
undoubtedly influence many other countries to adopt the same
course. 
</P>
</TEXT>
