<HEADLINE> 30 Killed, 1,000 Injured in India's Earthquake </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, May 22 (Xinhua) -- At least 30 people were killed
and about 1,000 others injured in an earthquake that hit Jabalpur
city of Madhya Pradesh state in India today.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here said that most of the victims died when
their houses collapsed under the impact of the earthquake
measuring 6.0 on the Richter scale. Thousands of people had
rendered homeless.
</P>
<P>
"People were jolted out of their sleep and all of them were
running around and looking for safety as they feared aftershocks,"
a local resident said.
</P>
<P>
Several thousand of houses were damaged in the quake, which
lasted for about 10 seconds, additional superintendent of police
for Jabalpur city Miss Sonali Mishra said.
</P>
<P>
Rescue and relief operations are in full swing. Rescuers
rummaged through the rubble of collapsed buildings to look for
trapped survivors.
</P>
<P>
President S.D. Sharma and Prime Minister I.K. Gujral expressed
their grief over the loss of lives and damage to properties in the
earthquake.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister, who is on a visit to northeastern states of
the country, had directed the cabinet secretary, T.S.R.
Subramaniam, to coordinate relief and rescue operations with the
state government.  
</P>
</TEXT>
