<HEADLINE> Talks Between Angolan President, Opposition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Angolan President Eduardo dos
Santos and opposition UNITA leader Jonas Savimbi should hold
talks as quickly as possible, Vice-President of the Social and
Democratic Party of Angola Nzuzi Sumbo said here today.
</P>
<P>
Sumbo told reporters that both sides have expressed their
willingness to hold talks and the people all over the country are
anxiously looking to them to do so.
</P>
<P>
Some of the problems existing in the peace process of Angola
could be resolved in the talks between the two leaders, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said, the establishment of local governments in the
southern African country is a very "important issue" which
demands a quick solution.
</P>
<P>
