<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Jumps 1 US Cent Overnight </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, May 22 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar jumped more
than one US cent overnight before closing above the 78 US cent
hurdle today.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar closed at 78.28, up from 77.65 at
Wednesday's close. It traded up 78.86 in New York overnight,
driven higher by technical factors.
</P>
<P>
A foreign exchange dealer at Colonial State Bank said the local
market had been heavy all day.
</P>
<P>
"People haven't seen these levels for a few weeks so local
people are taking the opportunity to sell," he said.
</P>
<P>
The recent volatility in the value of the US dollar continued
and a lift in its value overnight also helped the Australian
dollar's climb.
</P>
<P>
On the crosses, the Australian dollar closed firmer.
</P>
<P>
It finished at 90.54 Japanese yen up from 88.17 yen Wednesday
and at 1.3274 German marks up from 1.3071 marks.  
</P>
</TEXT>
