<HEADLINE> HK New Airport Core Program 80 Percent Complete </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 22 (Xinhua) -- More than 80 percent of work on
the 10 projects in Hong Kong's Airport Core Program (ACP) has been
finished when the 34 km transport corridor of the ACP is fully
open to traffic today.
</P>
<P>
An official release today said that by the end of March this
year, among the 10 projects, the seven government-funded ACP
projects had been about 96 percent complete and due to come to a
successful conclusion in the next two months.
</P>
<P>
In the months ahead, the New Airport Projects Coordination
Office (NAPCO) will focus its attention and efforts on the new
airport and the airport railway to ensure that they will be
completed on time and within budget.
</P>
<P>
"We will continue working closely with the Airport Authority
and the Mass Transit Railway Corporation in order to accomplish
the task of opening the airport and airport railway in April and
June respectively next year," said Billy Lam, director of NAPCO.
</P>
</TEXT>
