<HEADLINE> Fake Driving Licences Probed in S. Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, May 22 (Xinhua) -- The issuing of fraudulent
driver's licences is being probed throughout South Africa, the
local daily Citizen reported today.
</P>
<P>
In Gauteng Province alone, the issuing of about 5,000 fake
driver's licences was being investigated, the report said.
</P>
<P>
That represented only a small portion of real extent of the
probelm, Transport Department officials were quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
The process of checking the validity of 265,000 licences issued
countrywide between January 1995 and February 1996 was under way,
informed sources said.
</P>
<P>
Flem Meyer, driving inspectorate of the Transport Department, has
urged people to get legal licences and to report irregularities.
