<HEADLINE> Seminar on Raising Funds Overseas for Chinese Companies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Chinese enterprises can learn to be
more successful at raising funds overseas, according to a seminar
that opened in Beijing today.
</P>
<P>
The seminar was sponsored by the newspaper China Securities and
BZW Asia Limited, a division of Barclays Bank PLC. Participants
agreed that Chinese enterprises should use the opportunity to
raise funds in overseas markets because there is an incredible
amount of capital in developed Western countries that is looking
for ideal investment opportunities.
</P>
<P>
The three-day seminar attracted nearly 200 officials, experts,
and senior management personnel from the State Economic and Trade
Commission, the State Planning Commission, the People's Bank of
China, and the Development Research Center of the State Council,
as well as from large domestic and overseas financial institutions
and enterprises.
</P>
<P>
To date, 29 Chinese enterprises have been listed in Hong Kong,
New York, and London, raising a total of 5.9 billion US dollars.
