<HEADLINE> Nigeria Pays UN in Full </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria on Tuesday paid its contribution
to the 1997 United Nations budget in full, the official New
Nigerian reported today.
</P>
<P>
The report said Nigeria's Permanent Representative to the UN,
Ambassador Ibrahim Gambari delivered a cheque for 1.17 million
US dollars to James Connors, the UN Under-Secretary-General for
Administration and Management, in New York on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria is the 57th in the 185 UN member-countries that has paid up
its obligations. It is also the seventh African country, after South
Africa, Nambia, Egypt, Zimbabwe, Burkina Faso and Tunsia to do so, the
report said.
</P>
<P>
Gambari re-affirmed Nigeria's commitment to the UN and expressed
the hope that other member states would make the organization's job
easier by meeting their charter obligation, the report added. enditem
