<HEADLINE> Taliban Advance Blocked By Opposition Defector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, May 22 (Xinhua) -- A powerful defector of opposing
factions blocked the Afghan Islamic militia Taliban into the
capital of northwestern Faryab province despite Taliban's claims
that the defector joined its ranks, according to reports reaching
here today.
</P>
<P>
General Abdul Malik, who quit the ranks of Uzbek warlord Rashid
Dostum, has so far not allowed the Taliban to continue their
advance and enter into the provincial capital of Maimana, the
reports quoted sources there as saying.
</P>
<P>
Maimana is situated 220 kilometers (136 miles) west of
Mazar-i-Sharif, the headquarters of Dostum who is allied with the
ousted Afghan government and a Shiite-Moslem faction.
</P>
<P>
However, a Taliban spokesman denied the reports, claiming that
the joint Taliban-Malik forces are pushing into Dostum-controlled
neighboring Jowzjan province.
</P>
<P>
In a last-ditch effort, Dostum was said to have sent his
representatives to Faryab province for reconciliation with Malik.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that Dostum's representatives were trying to
persuade Malik to return to Dostum's side by warning him that the
Taliban would dump him once they complete their stronghold of
northern Afghanistan.  
</P>
