warrant 98 was the biggest loser as it declined by one dollar to
end at 9.7 Singapore dollars. The Development Bank of Singapore
(DBS) Foreign fell by 40 cents to close at 18.6 Singapore dollars,
while Bukit Sembawang finished 30 cents lower at 29.1 Singapore
dollars.  
