<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Turning Mountain Forests into Food Source </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, May 22 (Xinhua) -- China is using mountain forests to
get more food from xylophytes, or woody plants, in its search for
better ways to feed its growing population.
</P>
<P>
The country produces more than 1.8 billion kg of foodstuff from
woody plants annually and 160 million kg of oil, equivalent to 1.2
billion kg of paddy crops and 800 million kg of soybean,
respectively, according to a woody plant institute.
</P>
<P>
The mass production of food from woody plants not only helps
the ecology, but also provides abundant food and oil
supplies. China has more than 100 species of woody plants suitable
for food production, and over 200 kinds of trees suitable for oil,
and more than six million ha of xylophytes.
</P>
<P>
Farmers in Zhuji city in Zhejiang Province in east China turned
wasteland on mountainsides into arable land and planted Chinese
torreya (Torreya grandis), the fruit of which sold at more than 30
yuan per kg last year, making some growers rich as a result.
</P>
<P>
Woody plant food and oils are healthy as well, with their low
cholesterol, so demand for them is increasing. Food output from
major woody plants is expected to reach four billion kg and oil
output 1.1 billion kg by the end of the century.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970522.0179 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hubei to Hold Longevity Culture Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Zhongxiang City in central China's
Hubei Province is to hold a longevity culture and tourism festival
during the Double Ninth Festival, the Chinese seniors' day which
falls on the ninth day of September in the lunar calender.
</P>
<P>
During the festival, Chinese and foreign tourists will visit
villages with a number of people over 90 years old who will then
relate their experiences.
</P>
<P>
Zhongxiang City is located at the central part of Hubei
Province, and it is one of China's three areas where many people
enjoy long lifespan.
</P>
<P>
According to a nationwide census in 1990, the city, with a
population of 960,000, has 270 people above 90 years in age.
</P>
<P>
Apart from many cultural relic sites, Zhongxiang has a
state-level scenic spot-- the Dahong Mountain-- and a state-level
forest park.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
