<DOCNO> XIE19970522.0180 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Oldest Construction Remains Found in Hunan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, May 22 (Xinhua) -- A platform built in the late
Palaeolithic period (about two million - 10,000 years ago) has
been found in central China's Hunan province.
</P>
<P>
Chinese archaeologists say that the 0.7-m-high platform is the
oldest type of construction ever to be found in China.
</P>
<P>
The 24-sq.m. elliptical pounded-earth platform, built on top of
a larger six-m-high platform, has a square depression in the
middle and a four-m-long, 0.8-m-deep passage connecting the middle
with a gate on the southern side.
</P>
<P>
Small chipped stone tools were also found on the structure,
whose exact purpose has yet to be determined. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
