<HEADLINE> Malaysia, Italy to Enhance Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia and Italy today
discussed the ways to further enhance cooperation in various
fields, particularly on direct shipping of goods between the two
countries using Malaysia's largest Port Klang and Italian ports.
</P>
<P>
The discussions were held here between Malaysian Transport
Minister Ling Liong Sik and his Italian counterpart Claudio
Burlando who arrived here Wednesday for a two-day visit.
</P>
<P>
The two ministers also touched on how Italian and Malaysian
companies could invest in third countries having strong ties with
Malaysia such as Myanmar, Laos and Vietnam, Ling told reporters
after the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia Airlines (MAS) has been allowed to increase its weekly
flights to Rome from two to three, Ling said, adding he was
informed of the Italian government's approval on it during the
meeting.
</P>
<P>
Italian airport officials in the delegation led by Burlando
were also involved in discussions with officials of the Malaysian
Airport Corporation on future cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, during his meeting with the Italian minister here
today, Malaysian Acting Prime Minister Anwar Ibrahim proposed that
Malaysian and Italian investors set up joint ventures in the port,
waterway and airport sectors, especially in third countries.
</P>
<P>
The Italian minister and his delegation are scheduled to leave
here this evening for Singapore.  
</P>
</TEXT>
