<HEADLINE> China to Set up Museum of Commerce </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, May 22 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Ministry of Internal
Trade has decided to build a Commerce Museum in the scenic city of
Hangzhou, capital of coastal Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
The project will cover an 80,000-sq.m. area for a display
center for the history of Chinese commerce, an exposition center
for Chinese brand-name commodities, an international commercial
and cultural exchange center, and support facilities.
</P>
<P>
Total cost of the development is estimated at 400 million yuan
(48.2 million US dollars) and is expected to come from the
international trade ministry, Chinese enterprises, and overseas
investors.  
