<HEADLINE> China Social Science Academy Head Calls for Development of Marxism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Hu Sheng, president of the Chinese
Academy of Social Sciences, said here today that Marxism should be
further developed and adhered to.
</P>
<P>
"It is a great responsibility for social science researchers to
develop the theory," Hu said at a ceremony marking the academy's
20th anniversary.
</P>
<P>
Hu, a well-known Marxist scholar, said that researchers
should not avoid difficult and complicated problems, and should
confront new questions in economics, politics, social life, and
ideology, and should not simply draw conclusions from existing
books.
</P>
<P>
Any useful knowledge should be absorbed, he noted, so Marxism
can be enriched with new trends in various schools of thought.
</P>
<P>
The academy, which was previously a part of the Chinese Academy
of Sciences, is the country's top center of research in the
humanities and social sciences.  
</P>
</TEXT>
