<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Return Souvenirs Popular in Northeast China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, May 22 (Xinhua)-- Residents of Changchun, the
capital of northeast China's Jilin Province, are buying large
numbers of souvenirs commemorating the upcoming return of Hong
Kong to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
A thousand commemorative coins and 300 gold watches have
already sold out in a short time.
</P>
<P>
The gold watch has a portrait of Deng Xiaoping, the architect
of China's economic reforms, and the coins depict Tiananmen Square
and the Great Hall of the People in Beijing and the Central Plaza
in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
They were designed by Ling Feng, a professor at the Beijing
International Relations Institute, and have historical, artistic
and academic value, according to an expert at the Jilin Provincial
Collectors' Association.
</P>
<P>
One old customer said the souvenirs represent the hardships and
happiness of the Chinese people over the past 150 years, while a
young father said he bought the gold watch for his three-year-old
son to help him understand history through the commemorative coins
and watches. 
</P>
</TEXT>
