<HEADLINE> Cross-Century Calligraphy and Paintings Exhibition Held </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, May 22 (Xinhua) -- A calligraphy and painting exhibition
which will be held across the world til the beginning of the next
century opened last week in Weinan in northwest China's Shaanxi
Province.
</P>
<P>
The show, titled "Cross-Century Peace Painting Exhibition", was
sponsored jointly by China Association for the Advancement of
International Friendship and the other seven organizations from
China's inland area, Hong Kong and Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
The 518 art works from 11 countries and regions like Japan,
Malaysia and Singapore extols world peace, the return of Hong Kong
and expresses love for the motherland.
</P>
<P>
According to a local source, the show in Weinan will last for
ten days before moving to other parts of China and the rest of the
world until the spring of 2000.
</P>
<P>
"After the show some selected works will be presented to more
than 200 countries and regions as gifts," the source said. 
