<HEADLINE> East China Province Improving Machine-Building Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, May 22 (Xinhua) -- East China's Anhui Province has
scored some success in reshaping its machine-building industry,
increasing funding to more than 20 billion yuan last year, a 20
percent increase from the previous year.
</P>
<P>
The industry has implemented a pilot program for a modern
enterprises system in eight enterprises. This has helped them add
300 million yuan in assets and reduce assets-to-debt ratio
from 82 percent to 78 percent, using funding from different
sources, speeding up the movement of available assets, and
improving management.
</P>
<P>
Some 60 percent of state-owned enterprises are trying out a
modern enterprise system and 31 enterprises have introduced the
joint-stock system.
</P>
<P>
The province has given priority to large enterprises and has
set up 28 enterprise groups by mergers and by issuing stocks. Six
medium-sized and small machinery enterprises have begun to issue
stocks and 20 others have been merged, a move that is expected to
provide jobs for a large number of people in larger
undertakings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
