<HEADLINE> American Investors Eyeing Southwest China Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Investors from the US have
established 472 joint ventures in southwest China's Sichuan
Province, involving 380 million US dollars in investment, 28 of
which involved 10 million dollars each.
</P>
<P>
High-profile companies include Motorola, Pepsi Co., Coca-cola,
and McDonnell Aircraft.
</P>
<P>
U.S. investment accounted for 10.6 percent of total overseas
investment in Sichuan last year, and ranked third after Hong Kong
and Taiwan, said Li Dachang, provincial vice-governor. The
province's trade with the US made up 16.4 percent of its entire
foreign trade volume, he said.
</P>
<P>
Sichuan is located on the upper reaches of the Yangtze River
and has an abundance of natural resources, a large labor force,
and many scenic spots.
</P>
<P>
So far, 4,640 Sino-foreign joint ventures have come to Sichuan,
which leads all other provinces in central and western China.
</P>
<P>
Twelve major foreign banks, including Banque National De Paris,
Standard Chartered of Britain, and the Bank of Tokyo have branches
or representative offices in Sichuan, which plans to improve its
investment climate to introduce more overseas funds and advanced
technology in future, according to Li. 
</P>
</TEXT>
