<HEADLINE> Israel, Russia to Join Hands in Combating Crime </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Israel and Russia have agreed to
strenghthen cooperation in anti-mafia fight and is expected to
sign here today an agreement in this regard, the state-run Israel
Radio reported today.
</P>
<P>
Russian Interior Minister Anatoly Kulikov, who is also Russian
vice premier, held talks Wednesday with Israeli Public Security
Minister Avigdor Kahalani and Police Inspector-General Assaf Hefez
on cooperation in combating organized crimes.
</P>
<P>
The agreement is expected to be signed by Kulikov and Israeli
Deputy Prime Minister and Foreign Minister David Levy.
</P>
<P>
At the Wednesday meeting the two sides agreed to strengthen
cooperation and exchange of information in the case of Gregory
Lerner, a suspected Russian mafia leader operating in Israel.
</P>
<P>
Hefez said that detectives from Russia would come to Israel
to help investigate the case.
</P>
<P>
Kahalani said that he had prepared a list of names of 34
immigrants from the former Soviet Union whose Israeli
citizenship may be revoked on suspicion of involvement in the
Russian mafia.
</P>
<P>
Lerner, a multi-millionaire, was arrested and remanded for an
additional 12 days by Petah Tikva Magistrate's Court Sunday on
alleged charges of being one of the heads of the so-called Russia
mafia.
</P>
<P>
Lerner is refusing to cooperate with investigators and
emphatically denies any connection with organized crime.
</P>
<P>
But the National Crimes Squad believes that Lerner, who has
reportedly contributed hundreds of thousands of shekels (3.3
shekels equals to one U.S. dollar) to charities, the Ashkelon
Municipality, and Industry and Trade Minister Natan Shransky's
Yisrael Ba'aliya Party during the election campaign, is a
powerful and dangerous figure.
</P>
<P>
Police sources say that he is responsible for an
85-million-dollar bank fraud, the murder of a banker in Russia,
and conspiring to murder other bankers who refused to give him
money to open a bank in Israel. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
