<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Foreign Trade Booming in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Foreign Trade in Weihai, an open
coastal city in east China's Shandong Province, were worth 585
million US dollars in the first quarter of this year, with exports
up 68 percent from the same period of last year, and imports worth
123 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Some 56 percent of the total trade was handled by
foreign-funded enterprises. In the first quarter, there were 500
newly-established foreign-funded projects, using 71 million US
dollars of foreign funds, a 58 percent increase over the same
period of last year.
</P>
<P>
So far, 970 joint ventures have gone operational, generating
400 million yuan (48.2 million US dollars) in pre-tax profits in
the first quarter.
</P>
<P>
The processing trade in Weihai was worth 230 million US dollars
in the first quarter, accounting for 40 percent of the city's
total trade. 
</P>
