</P>
<P>
-- Ugandan President Yoweri Museveni on Wednesday advised
Zaire's leader Laurent Kabila to unite his country by forming a
broad-based government of national unity.
</P>
<P>
-- South African President Nelson Mandela on Wednesday slammed
Western nations for "lecturing" new Zairean leader Laurent Kabila
on democracy.
</P>
<P>
-- Dozens of people close to ousted Zairean President Mobutu
Sese Seko left Lome of Togo on Wednesday for the Chadian capital
Ndjamena, reliable sources said.
</P>
<P>
East African Standard
</P>
<P>
-- Opposition Democratic Party of Kenya on Wednesday called on
President Daniel arap Moi to organize a meeting between him and
opposition leaders, saying dialogue was the only way of avoiding
a situation similar to that in Zaire. 
</P>
