<HEADLINE> Malaysia's New Melaka State Chief Minister Appointed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia's Acting Prime
Minister Anwar Ibrahim today announced the appointment of Abu
Zahar Isnin as the new chief minister of Melaka (Malacca) state in
the south.
</P>
<P>
State executive councilor and assemblyman Abu Zahar will be the
new chief minister of the state effective tomorrow, Anwar told
reporters after receiving Italian Transport Minister Claudio
Burlando here.
</P>
<P>
Abu Zahar, 57, became Melaka's eighth chief minister to fill
the post left vacant following the death of former chief minister
of the state Mohd Zin Abdul Ghani of a stroke on May 14.
</P>
<P>
Anwar said that with the consent of Prime Minister Mahathir
Mohamad who is now on a two-month leave abroad, he has submitted
Abu Zahar's name to the Melaka Sultan Tun Syed Ahmad Shahabudin
for appointment as the new chief minister.
</P>
<P>
The acting prime minister said he was confident Abu Zahar could
serve well to continue to bring about development to Melaka.
</P>
<P>
Abu Zahar, a former teacher, once served as speaker of the
state Legislative Assembly and is currently the treasurer of
Melaka UMNO (United Malays National Organization, the backbone of
the ruling coalition headed by Mahathir).
</P>
<P>
Abu Zahar was first elected state assemblyman in 1986.
</P>
</TEXT>
