<HEADLINE> Security Tightened in Colombo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Police and the armed forces have
tightened security in Colombo in a bid to prevent possible Tamil
rebel attacks, police sources here said today.
</P>
<P>
According to the sources, a 12-member Black Tiger suicide squad
of the Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) has arrived in the
capital city.
</P>
<P>
Quoting intelligence reports, the sources said the squad had
been assigned to assassinate a key ruling party politician within
three months.
</P>
<P>
The threat posed by the Black Tiger suicide squad and measures
needed to counter it were discussed when the Colombo Security
Council met last Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Security units of three key government figures have been
informed of the new threat posed by the suicide squad, the sources
noted.
</P>
<P>
They added that all three services and police are involved in
security operations aimed at tracking down infiltrators.
</P>
<P>
Security check points have been increased on all the roads
leading to the capital city and the armed forces have reinforced
patrols at all the important facilities such as government
institutions, oil refineries, power stations, radio and TV
stations, according to defense sources here.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the LTTE rebels who have been fighting a 14-year
guerrilla war for a separate state in the country, launched
several major bomb attacks in the capital city.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
