<HEADLINE> Kazakhstan, EU to Boost Economic Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA ATA, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Kazakhstan and the European Union
said today they will strengthen cooperation in trade and
investment.
</P>
<P>
Kazakhstan has become an important economic partner of the EU,
according to documents released at a meeting held here by the two
sides.
</P>
<P>
There are now 200 companies from EU states in Kazakhstan, which
are playing an important role in the country. Bilateral
cooperation in the fields of energy, agriculture and
transportation is going on smoothly.
</P>
<P>
The Kazakh parliament and the European Parliament have ratified
the partnership and cooperation agreement the two sides signed in
January 1995.
</P>
<P>
The parliaments of the EU member states are expected to approve
the accord by the end of this year, which it is said will provide
a solid foundation for cooperation between the two sides. 
