<DOCNO> XIE19970522.0252 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Belarus to Revitalize Economy by 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Belarussian Prime Minister
Stepanovich Ling said in Minsk today that the economy will be
revitalized over the next three years, enabling the country to
enter the 21st century with prosperity.
</P>
<P>
In a short-term government working program submitted to
parliament, Ling said the economic stability which started last
year would be strengthened this year, the Itar-Tass news agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
Under the program, state-owned companies will be divided into
semi-privatized and private companies. The government will give
full support to the development of key enterprises and help
relieve them of the burden of excess costs such as welfare
payments.
</P>
<P>
The program also requires the government to reduce the use of
barter in trade and further open the foreign currency market.
</P>
<P>
Ling stressed that his government would neither carry out
complete privatization, or turn all land over to private
ownership, nor dissolve all the collective or state-owned farms.
</P>
<P>
Belarus' economy began to recover last year after several years
of recession following independence in 1991. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970522.0253 </DOCNO>
