<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia Supports "Land For Peace" in Middle East Peace Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Russian Foreign Minister Yevgeny
Primakov said today the Middle East peace process should continue
on the basis of "land for peace."
</P>
<P>
Primakov told a press conference here after meeting with his
Syrian counterpart, Farouq al-Shara, that Israel should return all
the Arab lands it occupied during the Middle East wars.
Otherwise, there would be no "just peace" based on security for
all countries in the region.
</P>
<P>
Primakov supports a strengthened European role in the Middle
East peace process.
</P>
<P>
Shara said he hoped that Israel would change its stand and put
the peace process back on the right track.
</P>
<P>
Tension occurred when the Israeli government decided to carry
out a plan to build Jewish settlements in East Jerusalem early
this year.
</P>
<P>
Al-Shara, who had a telephone conversation with Russian
President Boris Yeltsin earlier in the day, said that Syria is
satisfied with Russia's stand that Israel should return the Golan
Heights to Syria. 
</P>
