<HEADLINE> Vietnamese Party Leader Arrives in Yangon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Vietnamese Communist Party General
Secretary Do Muoi arrived here today on a four-day official visit
to Myanmar.
</P>
<P>
Do Muoi paid the visit at the invitation of Senior-General Than
Shwe, chairman of the Myanmar State Law and Order Restoration
Council, who visited Vietnam in March 1995.
</P>
<P>
It is the second visit to Myanmar by a Vietnamese leader in
three years since Prime Minister Vo Van Kiet visited the country
in May 1994.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders are expected to have official discussions on
bilateral relations and regional issues to further strengthen
friendly relations and cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
</TEXT>
