<HEADLINE> Albanian Currency Devaluated </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, May 21 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. dollar was quoted at 166
lek Wednesday on the Tirana foreign exchange market as against
159.5 the previous day.
</P>
<P>
The Albanian currency has devaluated by about 65 percent so far
this year. As a result, the prices of foods and industrial
products, especially imported goods have risen sharply, causing
worries among Albanians. 
</P>
