<DOCNO> XIE19970522.0258 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Opens New Airport Link </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's Lantau Link
officially opened to road traffic at 8:00 this morning to become
the first highway connection between Lantau Island and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Lantau Link is the key element in the 34-km direct road and
rail network leading to the New Airport at Chek Lap Kok. Thousands
of people are expected to drive through the link today.
</P>
<P>
A computer-based control system has been installed to monitor
and regulate traffic flow along the entire 34 km road system known
as the Tsing Ma Control Area.
</P>
<P>
Part of the link is the 2.2 km Tsing Ma Bridge, which is the
world's longest suspension bridge capable of carrying both road
and rail traffic.
</P>
<P>
With today's opening of the link, people are now able to drive
from Central on Hong Kong Island, through the newly-opened Western
Harbor Crossing, along the West Kowloon Expressway and Route 3,
across two sea channels to Lantau Island and finally reach the New
Airport along the North Lantau Highway.
</P>
<P>
According to schedule, the New Airport will start operation in
1988, by which time the airport railway will be opened.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
