<HEADLINE> Clinton Meets, Black Lawmakers Meet on Racial Issues </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, May 21 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton and
more than a dozen black lawmakers today discussed a number of
issues related to racial reconciliation, said members of the
Congressional Black Caucus.
</P>
<P>
Black Caucus members said that during an hour-long meeting,
Clinton took note of the issues they raised, including urban
school renovations, public hospital closings, the plight of black
farmers and U.S. policy in Africa.
</P>
<P>
White House officials reportedly confirmed that the possibility
of a White House conference on race relations was discussed, but
said a final decision had not yet been made.
</P>
<P>
Clinton has promised a major initiative on race, and he plans
to start it with an address on the subject on June 14 at the
University of San Diego. 
</P>
