<HEADLINE> Industrial Output Across China Increases in March </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 22 (Xinhua) -- China's 31 provinces,
municipalities and autonomous regions generated 440.45 billion
yuan in industrial output in the first quarter this year, up 16.06
percent over the corresponding period of 1996, according to the
latest statistics from State Statistical Bureau.
</P>
<P>
In the January-March period, Jiangsu, Guangdong and Shanghai
ranked the top three industrial manufacturers, turning out 61.5
billion yuan, 43.7 billion yuan and 33.3 billion yuan, in output
value respectively. 
