<HEADLINE> Delta Programme Under Way </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 22 (Xinhua) -- The first sustainable development
project under a program geared for the 21st century has been
agreed in China, today's "China Daily" reports.
</P>
<P>
The first project of the UN-sponsored environmental protection
program for China is focused on development and conservation in
the Yellow River Delta.
</P>
<P>
Experts have completed a panoramic development plan based on a
two-year feasibility study on the economic development, ecosystem,
environment and natural resources in the delta areas.
</P>
<P>
It is the first project out of China's 62 priority programs to
receive the United Nations Development Program (UNDP) assistance.
</P>
<P>
Progress has been made in the project since it was started in
March 1995. More efforts are still needed for water resource
management, water quality surveillance and flood prevention and
control in the Yellow River Delta, said an official at the
Ministry of Transport, Public Works and Water Management of the
Netherlands, which is devoted to the development of the delta.
</P>
<P>
The delta development will benefit the northern and part
of central China. The delta, abundant in land, water, oil, tourism
and natural resources, was listed as a major production base for
grain and cotton by the state in 1995. The paper said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
