<HEADLINE> Dual Listing For B-Share Firm </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 22 (Xinhua) -- Southeast Electric Power Co will
become the first B-share company to have a dual listing in
Shanghai and London, today's "China Daily" reports.
</P>
<P>
The paper quotes Huan Guocang, managing director of BZW's
investment banking division as saying that as a division of
Barclays Bank, BZW is acting as an international co-ordinator for
the power company, expecting to make the initial public offerings
of B-shares in Shanghai and global depositary shares in London
early this summer.
</P>
<P>
B shares are issued domestically but are traded in foreign
currency to encourage foreign investors.
</P>
<P>
The power company wants to pool about 100 million US dollars
through the stock market.
</P>
<P>
BZW is responsible for all wholesale banking, securities
dealing and investment banking services within the Barclays
Group. It recently acted as sponsor and lead manager to the
initial public offerings and global placing of H shares by
Zhejiang Expressway Co Ltd.  
</P>
