<HEADLINE> Mexican Entrepreneurs Interested in Investing in Nicaragua </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANAGUA, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Several Mexican companies have
expressed their interest in investing in Nicaragua when a
Nicaraguan business group visited Mexico, the Nicaragua's Foreign
Ministry said today.
</P>
<P>
The Nicaraguan delegation, headed by Eugenio Lacayo, general
director of economy and foreign trade under the Foreign Ministry,
traveled to Monterrey in the state of Nuevo Leon in Mexico and met
with business executives of the cement company Cemex, the Nuevo
Leon regional cattle ranchers union, Parras Hilaturas, Comercial
Bento the Maseca industrial group and supermarkets.
</P>
<P>
The Foreign Ministry said that Cemex plans to build a cement
factory while the Maseca industrial group is interested in
building a cornmeal plant and planting maize in western Nicaragua.
</P>
<P>
The Nuevo Leon regional cattle ranchers union expressed its
desire to participate in the "Expica" fair which is held every
year in Nicaragua and invited the Nicaraguan Chamber of Cattle
Ranchers to take part in fairs held in Mexico.
</P>
<P>
Hilaturas Parras, a company which produces denim for blue
jeans, will send representatives to Nicaragua soon to explore the
possibility of planting cotton and installing an assembly plant in
Nicaragua.
</P>
<P>
Comercial Bento, a pharmaceutical laboratory, will set up a
laboratory in Nicaragua. 
</P>
