regulation that bans state-owned enterprises and listed companies
from stock speculation.
</P>
<P>
The commentary, entitled "A good method to promote the
standardized development of the stock market," described the
regulation as an "appropriate prescription for promoting sound
growth of the state-owned enterprises and curbing over-speculation
on the stock market."
</P>
<P>
-- President Jiang Zemin said here yesterday that China
respects the Hungarian people in choosing their road of
development and is willing to further co-operation between the
two countries in various fields.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said during a meeting with Gal Zoltan, president of the
National Assembly of Hungary, that such co-operation will be based
on the principle of mutual respect, equality and mutual benefit,
and mutual non-interference into each other's internal affairs.
</P>
<P>
