<HEADLINE> Austria, Germany Agree on EU, NATO Expansion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Both Austria and Germany support an
enlargement of the European Union to take in east European
countries, Austrian President Thomas Klestil and visiting German
President Roman Herzog told reporters here today.
</P>
<P>
After holding talks on EU enlargement and the eastward
expansion plans of the North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO),
the two presidents agreed that the 15-nation union should be
enlarged to include countries in eastern Europe.
</P>
<P>
Herzog, who arrived here earlier today for a three-day visit to
Austria, said that Germany and Austria should not be the EU's
eastern frontier forever. Both countries wanted the union to
expand eastward out of "selfishness" and the desire to unite east
European nations.
</P>
<P>
Asked if Austria would join NATO, Klestil said the question was
still under discussion. He said the government will consider its
position after the military alliance's summit in Madrid in July.
</P>
<P>
During his stay, Herzog will also meet Austrian Federal
Chancellor Viktor Klima and Foreign Minister Wolfgang Schussel.
</P>
</TEXT>
