<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Foreign investments entering Chile
during the first quarter increased by 8.5 percent to 1.47 billion
U.S. dollars, compared with the same period in 1996, said a report
released by the Foreign Investment Committee today.
</P>
<P>
