<HEADLINE> Direct Foreign Capital Drops in Venezuela </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Foreign investments in Venezuela
decreased by 28.9 percent in the first four months of this year,
compared with the same period in 1996, the Venezuelan Ministry of
Industry and Commerce reported today.
</P>
<P>
Foreign capital flows totaled 91.9 million U.S. dollars between
January-April of this year when the foreign capital amounted to
127.8 million dollars compared with the same period of 1996, the
ministry said in a report published today.
</P>
<P>
The investments exclude those reported in the financial sectors
(including capital markets), insurance, hydrocarbons,
petrochemicals and the coal, mining and related industries.
</P>
<P>
Financial services, companies and real estate firms received
38.88 million dollars of foreign capital; agriculture and
livestock 35.58 million dollars and the manufacturing sector 15.57
million dollars.
</P>
<P>
The highest volume of foreign investments in Venezuela came
from the British Virgin Islands with 17.88 million dollars,
followed by the United States with 13.4 million, Canada with 10.76
million and South Korea with 6.7 million dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
