<HEADLINE> Italy, Russia Launch Mobile Phone JV </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Nuova Telespaszio, a subsidiary of
Italy's state-owned telecommunications monopoly Stet, is to set up
a joint venture company with Russia's Inforcosmos to sell mobile
phones in Russia.
</P>
<P>
The company, Marems, will be headquartered in Moscow, with the
Russian side holding 51 percent of the shares.
</P>
<P>
Marems will provide satellite mobile phone services later this
year for voice and data transmission and emergencies and will
offer users access to the land-based international network from
anywhere in Russia.
</P>
<P>
Target customers will be the international and domestic
long-haul transport sector, regional users in areas uncovered by
the Global System for Mobile (GSM) communications service, as well
as public and government institutions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
