<HEADLINE> Illegal Albanian Immigrants, Border Conflicts Worry Macedonia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, May 21 (Xinhua) -- More than 300 cases of illegal
Albanian immigrants and 34 border conflicts have occurred on the
Macedonian-Albanian border in the past five months, a Macedonian
defense ministry spokesman said today.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said a group of Albanian cigarette smugglers
trying to cross the border of the two countries ran into conflict
with border guards on May 19. A Finnish soldier of the
U.N. Protective Deployment Force in Macedonia was hit by a stray
bullet in the conflict.
</P>
<P>
Macedonian Defense Minister Blagoj Handziski visited the site
of the incident on May 20 and ordered the Macedonian border troops
to be on high alert.
</P>
<P>
On May 13, some armed Albanians illegally crossed the border
into Macedonia and exchanged fire with Macedonian policemen,
leaving one Albanian and two Macedonians dead. 
