<HEADLINE> South Korea Beats England to Join China, Indonesia, Denmark </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GLASGOW, Scotland, May 21 (Xinhua) -- World number eight Park
Sung Woo suffered a shock defeat by Englishman Darren Hall as
South Korea beat England 4-1 in a Group A match in Sudirman Cup
badminton competition here Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
The South Korean victory means that defending champion China
and South Korea are all guaranteed a berth in the semi-finals as
each registerd one victory while England would definitely finished
bottom in the group with two losses.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia and Denmark in Group B also entered the last four
with similar situation, with Sweden being the bottom team.
</P>
<P>
Ra Kyung Min, half of the Olympic mixed doubles runner-up pair,
teamed up with Kim Dong Moon to overcome Simon Archer and Julie
Bradbury 15-13, 15-11 in the opening mixed doubles match.
</P>
<P>
Park Sung Woo, the 1995 world championship runner-up,
surprisingly lost the first game of the men's singles match to
57-th ranked Hall in the men's singles 10-15.
</P>
<P>
Park staged a spectacular come-back in the second game and led
14-9. But Hall, combining delicate net play with clever smashes,
rallied to tie it 14-14 before winning 17-15.
</P>
<P>
The rest of the English camp, despite receiving a vocal support
from the stands, were apparently no match for the South Koreans.
</P>
<P>
Olympic semi-finalist Kim Ji Kyun beat Julia Mann 11-5, 11-1 in
the women's singles, All-England men's doubles champion Kang Kyung
Jin and Ha Tae Kwon rolled over Chris Hunt and Simon Archer 15-8,
15-8, while Kim Shin Young and Chung Jae Hee beat Julie Bradbury
and Donna Kellogg 15-9, 15-8 in the women's doubles.
</P>
<P>
China, will face South Korea in Thursday's last group A match
and vie for the group winner position.
</P>
<P>
In the semi-finals, Group A winner will meet group B runner-up
and vice versa. The final is slated for Saturday. 
</P>
