<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Bettina Wiegmann, midfielder of German
women's national soccer team, was voted Germany's Footballer of
the Year in 1997 in Munich on Wednesday after beating 14 other
candidates.
</P>
<P>
Soccer legend Franz Beckenbauer, a member of the voting
committee, presented the Hermes Cup for the award to the
26-year-old.
</P>
<P>
