<HEADLINE> Ireland Beats Liechtenstein 5-0 in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, May 21 (Xinhua) -- David Connolly scored a first-half
hat-trick as Ireland beat Liechtenstein 5-0 in a World Cup
European group eight qualifying match in Dublin on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Connolly, 19, opened the scoring in the 28th minute when he
chipped into an empty net from six meters.
</P>
<P>
He scored his second seven minutes later when he ran on to a
brilliant through-pass from captain Andy Townsend and slotted
the ball home low to goalkeeper Martin Heeb's left.
</P>
<P>
Connolly completed his hat-trick in the 41st minute on a cross
from a teammate, tapping the ball home from point-blank range.
</P>
<P>
Striker Tony Cascarino added two more goals in the 60th and
78th minutes, receiving deep crosses from defender Jeff Kenna and
sending headers into the roof of the net. 
