<HEADLINE> Denmark Defeats Sweden to Enter Semi with Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GLASGOW, Scotland, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Denmark defeated Sweden
4-1 to win its first group B match in top Division 1 here on
Wednesday and gained a semi-final spot at the Sudirman Cup world
mixed team badminton championship.
</P>
<P>
Sweden had two losses and doomed to finish bottom in the
group. Indonesia, which beat Sweden 5-0 Tuesday, and Denmark will
advance to the semi-finals despite the outcome of Thursday's clash
between them.
</P>
<P>
European and Swiss Open champion Camilla Martin of Denmark had
an easy win over unheralded Swede Marina Andrievskaya 11-3, 11-3
to take the opening women's singles match.
</P>
<P>
Last season's World Grand Prix finals winning pair Michael
Sogaard and Rikke Olsen had little trouble to beat Jens Olsson and
Astrid Crabo of Sweden 15-6, 15-3 in the following mixed doubles.
</P>
<P>
But Denmark's world number ten and Korean Open titlist Thomas
Stuer-Lauridsen had to survive a first-game thrill to beat Rikard
Magnusson 18-14 after the two drew 14-all. He waked up to win the
second game 15-1 and put Denmark into an unbeatable 3-0 lead.
</P>
<P>
Thomas Stavngaard and Jim Laugensen made it 4-0 for the Danes
by beating Peter Axelsson and Par Gunnar Jonsson 15-11 and 17-14
in the men's doubles.
</P>
<P>
Sweden, who lost to Indonesia on Tuesday, saved part of its
face after Andrievskaya teamed up with Catrine Bengtsson and
defeated Lisbet Stuer-Lauridsen and Marlene Thomsen 15-9, 15-3 in
the women's doubles.
</P>
<P>
The victory of Thursday's Indonesia-Denmark clash will win the
group and take on the runner-up from group A. 
</P>
</TEXT>
