<HEADLINE> Schalke Wins UEFA Cup Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MILAN, May 21 (Xinhua) -- Schalke of Germany won the UEFA
soccer cup final here today after a penalty shoot-out against
Internazionale of Milan.
</P>
<P>
The two teams were level 1-1 on aggregate after Internazionale
completed tonight's second leg 1-0 ahead, matching Schalke's 1-0
victory in the first leg two weeks ago.
</P>
<P>
Inter's goal was scored by Ivan Zamorano in the 39th minute of
the second half.
</P>
<P>
However Schalke won the penalty shoot-out when Zamorano missed
the first of Inter's attempts and Winter the third while the
German players were all on target. 
</P>
